The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Washington, July 20: India will receive about $4.5 billion from the International Monetary Funds special drawing rights (SDR) to battle the economic slowdown. This is part of the $250-billion allocation by the IMF to provide liquidity to the global economic system by supplementing IMFs 186 member countries foreign exchange reserves. The funds would be available at the end of August, IMF officials said.                            
	 New Delhi, July 20: Gold imports fell 50 per cent in June compared with the same period last year. Gold imports stood at 12 tonnes in June 2009 compared with 24 tonnes in the same month last year, according to the Bombay Bullion Association.                             
	 New Delhi, July 20: The United States Securities and Exchange Commission, the federal agency which regulates the securities business in the US, has sought the permission of the Indian government and the CBI to probe the multi-million dollar Satyam fraud case, CBI director Ashwani Kumar said.                                                                                                                           
